Parameter.Name: RdneMappingType
Parameter.Comment: This setting is used by the rdnemapping.so to determine the mapping to be used for this feed - for cta it should always be set to "siac"

DefineParameterGroup.Name: CtaRetransParams
DefineParameterGroup.Comment: Common params used by the retrans lines.

Parameter.Name: TcpHeartbeatInterval
Parameter.Comment: CTA expects no heartbeat messages to be sent on live connections.

Parameter.Name: CtaAlwaysConnectToRetransLines
Parameter.Comment: This parameter overrides TcpConnectOnStartUp. When this parameter is true the feed handler will connect to the multicast retrans lines during startup and remain connected while the feed handler is running. When this parameter is false the feed handler will only connect to the multicast retrans lines when retrans is required, and then the feed handler will disconnect after the retrans is finished.

Parameter.Name: CtaRetransMaxQueuedRequests
Parameter.Comment: The maximal number of the retrans requests staying in the queue. Once the queue is longer than this value (mostly because of too many retrans requests in a short time frame), the queue will be cleared for responding to the most lastest requests

Parameter.Name: CtaRetransMaxReconnectCount
Parameter.Comment: The maximal number of reconnecting to GRP server. Every try will be delayed "TcpConnectDelay" millseconds.

Parameter.Name: CtaRetransRequestGapLimit
Parameter.Comment: The maximal number of gap for each retrans request. Not like LineFilterGapLimit, any gap request over this number will be split into a group of requests.

Parameter.Name: CtaRetransExtraLogging
Parameter.Comment: Set to true to get more logging on Cta Proxy line (useful during testing and debugging)
